void select_n_init::sync_with_sum_func_and_with_field()
{
  /*
    This function is used to handle the following case:

    SELECT a, SUM(b) FROM t GROUP BY a;

    In this case we need to make sure that all items in the SELECT list
    are evaluated before any item in the SUM() list. This is required
    since the SUM() list is evaluated before the items in the SELECT
    list.

    The flag with_sum_func is used to determine if an item has been
    evaluated before any SUM() item. The flag with_field is used to
    determine if an item has been evaluated before any field (in the
    current row). The flag with_param is used to determine if an item
    has been evaluated before any parameter marker (in the current
    query). The function of each item is to set the appropriate flag
    before it is evaluated.

    An exception is when an item has been put in the SELECT list because
    of an HAVING clause. In this case the flag with_field is set for the
    item, since it will be evaluated after the GROUP BY (and HAVING)
    have been evaluated).

    The List_iterator_fast will iterate over the items in the SELECT
    list, and for each item will iterate over the SUM() items to
    determine if the item has been evaluated before any of them.
